Unknown Type.description: Sprague's Pipits have streaked or scaled upperparts and a paler face unlike American Pipits, which have an unstreaked back and a darker looking face with an eyering. Sprague's don't bob their tails like American Pipits.
Vesper Sparrows have a smaller conical bill and a streaked back unlike American Pipits, which have an unstreaked back and a thin bill.
